# ========================================
# Setup Instructions
# ========================================
# 1. Database Setup (Neon):
#    - Sign up at https://neon.tech
#    - Create a new project
#    - Copy the connection string to DATABASE_URL
#    - Run: npm run db:push (to create tables)
#
# 2. Session Secret:
#    - Generate a random string (min 32 characters)
#    - You can use: node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
#
# 3. OAuth Providers (Optional - choose one or more):
#    
#    Google:
#    - Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
#    - Create OAuth 2.0 Client ID
#    - Add authorized redirect URI: https://your-domain/api/callback/google
#    - Copy Client ID and Client Secret
#    
#    GitHub:
#    - Go to https://github.com/settings/developers
#    - Create new OAuth App
#    - Add callback URL: https://your-domain/api/callback/github
#    - Copy Client ID and Client Secret
#    
#    LinkedIn:
#    - Go to https://www.linkedin.com/developers/apps
#    - Create new app
#    - Add redirect URL: https://your-domain/api/callback/linkedin
#    - Copy Client ID and Client Secret
#
# 4. Email Setup (Resend via Replit Connectors):
#    - If using Replit: Connect Resend in the Replit UI
#    - Otherwise: Modify server/email.ts to use direct Resend API key
#
# 5. For local development:
#    - Set REPLIT_DOMAINS=localhost
#    - Ensure DATABASE_URL points to your database
#    - At least one OAuth provider should be configured
# ========================================
